Lexington-Fayette.Odd Fellows Temple (Lexington, Kentucky):
The Odd Fellows Temple in Lexington, Kentucky, also known as Skullers Jewelry, Inc., was built in Second Empire and Italianate style in 1869-70. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1980.
It is a 41 feet (12 m) by 97 feet (30 m) building that is primarily Italianate in style, but has a Second Empire-styled top floor.
